  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "For GKE, we have a goal of securing the node -> master communication completely, and eliminating it where we can. Rather than head down the rathole of making sure Salt is secure, I decided to look and see how hard it would be just to convert each VM to a standalone SaltStack configuration, ala: http://docs.saltstack.com/en/latest/topics/tutorials/quickstart.html\n\nIt turns out, this that isn't hard at all, and completely eliminates node -> master Salt communication. It also spells doom and gloom for any \"dynamic configuration story\" using Salt, but I fixed up `kube-push` for GCE in the process as well, at least, so there's that.\n",
